<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1586,2015]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1846,1871]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Clark" box="[326,704,1846,1871]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refString="Clark, A. &amp; Courtman-Stock, J. (1976) The Echinoderms of Southern Africa. Publication no. 766. British Museum of Natural History, London, 277 pp." type="book" year="1976">Clark &amp; Courtman-Stock (1976)</bibRefCitation>
have flagged Clark’s (1923 &amp; 1924) East coast record of the species as they point out it “is queried by Mortensen as unlikely to refer to this Atlantic species; at least one locality off Natal is duplicated by the British Museum specimen which proved to be referable to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doderlein" authorityYear="1901" box="[1165,1417,1918,1943]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinothuriidae" genus="Sperosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echinothurioida" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="biseriatum">
<emphasis box="[1165,1417,1918,1943]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sperosoma biseriatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”. Differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. L. Clark" authorityYear="1924" box="[300,578,1955,1978]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinothuriidae" genus="Araeosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echinothurioida" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="paucispinum">
<emphasis box="[300,578,1955,1978]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Araeosoma paucispinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in arrangement of pore-pairs, where 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Mortensen" authorityYear="1935" box="[998,1220,1955,1978]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinothuriidae" genus="Hygrosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echinothurioida" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="petersii">
<emphasis box="[998,1220,1955,1978]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Hygrosoma petersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has pore-pairs in a single series and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. L. Clark" authorityYear="1924" box="[343,517,1991,2014]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinothuriidae" genus="Araeosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echinothurioida" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="paucispinum">
<emphasis box="[343,517,1991,2014]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">A. paucispinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in oblique arcs forming three ventral series.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
